From 1acdf3b28c916614b5cc6a929bb4efa146ff340c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 11:49:58 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(identity): make the public-github identity gate
 host-aware
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The proactive noreply-identity gate (#762/#785) stripped the host from a
remote before resolving visibility, so a non-github remote (e.g. a
gitlab.com SSH URL) collapsed to a bare owner/repo slug that gh repo
view then resolved against github.com. If a public github.com repo
existed at that owner/repo, a non-github clone could be stamped with the
public GitHub noreply identity instead of its inherited identity.

- Add is_github_host()/_host_from() and gate is_public_github_remote on a
  github.com (or github.com-<ssh-alias>) host BEFORE any gh call.
- Pass the full remote URL (host intact) from both call sites
  (WorktreeProvisioner, workspace stamp-identity) — never the
  host-stripped slug.
- Tests: a gitlab/bitbucket host short-circuits to False with no gh call;
  a non-github worktree keeps its inherited identity even when gh would
  answer PUBLIC for the host-stripped slug; github + ssh-alias hosts still
  stamp.
---
